# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# HRMS Environment Variables — Reference (v24·0625)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to `.env` (local dev) or set these in Vercel Project Settings
# → Environment Variables (production).
#
# VARIABLES ARE GROUPED BY PURPOSE:
#   1. Database (required)
#   2. ERP↔HRMS Attendance Bridge (required for the v24·0625 integration)
#   3. ERP↔HRMS Leave Integration (required for leave sync)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1) DATABASE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: SQLite file
DATABASE_URL="file:/home/z/my-project/db/custom.db"
# Production (Vercel + Neon): PostgreSQL connection string from Neon dashboard
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require"
# Neon also provides DIRECT_URL — set it to the same value if your schema uses it.
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require"

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2) ERP ↔ HRMS ATTENDANCE BRIDGE (v24·0625)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HRMS_BRIDGE_API_KEY — shared secret that ERP sends in `x-hrms-api-key` header
#                       when ERP calls HRMS's GET /api/external/attendance
#                       to read an employee's attendance (read-only).
#                       Use a long random string (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`).
HRMS_BRIDGE_API_KEY=""

# ERP_BRIDGE_URL — base URL of the ERP deployment (no trailing slash).
#                  Used by HRMS to call ERP's external attendance-query API.
#                  e.g. "https://erp-ea.vercel.app"
ERP_BRIDGE_URL="https://erp-ea.vercel.app"

# ERP_BRIDGE_API_KEY — shared secret that HRMS sends in `x-erp-api-key` header
#                      when calling ERP's:
#                        GET  /api/external/attendance-queries
#                        PATCH /api/external/attendance-queries/[id]/respond
#                      This must EXACTLY match the value set as ERP_BRIDGE_API_KEY
#                      in the ERP project's Vercel env vars.
ERP_BRIDGE_API_KEY=""

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3) ERP ↔ HRMS LEAVE INTEGRATION (existing — leave sync)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional — only needed if you use the leave sync feature. If unset,
# the integration falls back to a default key (NOT recommended for production).
HRMS_ERP_INTEGRATION_KEY=""
# ERP_BASE_URL is used by the leave sync helper. Defaults to the ERP prod URL
# if unset. Override here if you need to point at a different ERP env.
# ERP_BASE_URL="https://erp-ea.vercel.app"

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP CHECKLIST (do these in order after deploying both projects):
#   1. Generate two strong random strings:
#        HRMS_BRIDGE_API_KEY=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
#        ERP_BRIDGE_API_KEY=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
#   2. On ERP (Vercel) set:
#        HRMS_BRIDGE_URL     = https://hrms-xxx.vercel.app   (HRMS prod URL)
#        HRMS_BRIDGE_API_KEY = <the value generated above>
#        ERP_BRIDGE_API_KEY  = <the value generated above>   (same on both sides)
#   3. On HRMS (Vercel) set:
#        HRMS_BRIDGE_API_KEY = <same value as ERP>            (HRMS verifies inbound)
#        ERP_BRIDGE_URL      = https://erp-ea.vercel.app      (ERP prod URL)
#        ERP_BRIDGE_API_KEY  = <same value as ERP>            (HRMS sends outbound)
#   4. Apply the additive SQL script (download/v24-apply-additive-schema.sql)
#      on ERP's Neon Postgres to create the AttendanceQuery table.
#   5. Redeploy both projects so the new env vars take effect.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
